# Log Warning Fixer

Used when the log-watcher `stop` hook submits a queued entry, or when explicitly asked to drain/fix log warnings.

Queued line types:
- `PHP Warning`, `PHP Deprecated`, `PHP Fatal error` (maps `cache/templates_c/` back to `layouts/` when possible)
- Application `[error]` and `[warning]` lines from FreeCRM logging (including `=> /path/file.php:line`)

Not queued: `[info]`, request dumps, `vendor/`, or paths with no source file on disk.
Activity and skip reasons: `.cursor/log-watcher.log` (use `tail -f` here — the queue stays empty when lines are deduped or already drained).

Dedupe: each log line gets a key in `.cursor/log-warnings.seen`. The stop hook removes that key when it pops the item, so a warning can re-enter the queue if it still appears after a fix attempt. Only one background watcher should run (`start-log-watcher.sh` enforces this on reload).

## Scope

- Fix **one** warning per turn.
- Edit `src/` or `layouts/` only.
- Never edit `vendor/`, `cache/templates_c/`, or generated files.
- Docker log paths use `/var/www/html/` — map to the project root.

## Smarty warnings

- Warnings in `cache/templates_c/*.php` come from a `.tpl` under `layouts/`.
- Fix the template source, then: `rm -f cache/templates_c/*.php`

## Fix patterns (modern PHP)

| Pattern | Approach |
|---------|----------|
| `Passing null to parameter` | Guard caller or default before the call |
| `Undefined array key` | Fix data flow or use `??` when the key is legitimately optional |
| `Undefined property` | Add typed property, initialize in constructor, or fix accessor — avoid blind `@` suppression |
| Smarty unregistered function/class | Register via Smarty bootstrap, not in templates |
| Fatal `Failed opening required` | Fix include path or guard missing prerequisites |

## Verification

1. Prefer reproducing via the web UI (see `error-checking.mdc`).
2. Ignore CLI-only warnings if web context is clean.
3. Do not consider the warning fixed until it stops appearing in `cache/logs/system.log` for that code path.

## Queue state

Runtime files (gitignored): `.cursor/log-warnings.queue`, `.cursor/log-warnings.seen`, `.cursor/log-watcher.pid`

To reset deduplication and re-queue all warnings: stop the watcher, delete `.cursor/log-warnings.seen`, restart Cursor or run `.cursor/hooks/start-log-watcher.sh`.
